definition.value: A member of the class of  sulfamides that is N,N-dimethylsulfuric diamide substituted by a 4-methylphenyl group at the amino nitrogen atom. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical tolylfluanid.
A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazin-2-ol substituted by a tert-butylamino group at position 4 and an ethylamino group at position 6. It is a metabolite of the herbicide terbutylazine,

A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole that is substituted at positions 1, 3, 4, and 5 by 2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl, cyano, (trifluoromethyl)sulfonyl, and amino groups, respectively. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical fipronil.

A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole that is substituted at positions 1, 3, 4, and 5 by 2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl, cyano, (trifluoromethyl)sulfanyl, and amino groups, respectively. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical fipronil.

A member of the class of pyrazoles that is 1H-pyrazole that is substituted at positions 1, 3, 4, and 5 by 2,6-dichloro-4-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl, cyano, trifluoromethyl, and amino groups, respectively.
A member of the class of pradimicins that is isolated from the cultured broth of Actinomadura hibisca No. P157-2 (ATCC 53557).
A pyridone that is pyridin-2(1H)-one substituted by chloro groups at positions 3, 5 and 6. It is a metabolite of the agrochemical chlorpyrifos.

A monocarboxylic acid that is perfluorinated hexanoic acid.

An aryloxypyrimidine having a 4,6-diphenoxypyrimidine skeleton in which one of the phenyl rings is cyano-substituted at C-2 and the other carries a 1-carboxy-2-methoxyethenyl substituent, also at C-2. It is a metabolite of the fungicidal agrochemical azoxystrobin.
A sulfoxide derivative of the drug ranitidine.
A N-oxide derivative of ranitidine.

A dipeptide composed of N-(3,3-dimethylbutyl)-L-aspartic acid and methyl L-phenylalanate units joined by a peptide linkage.
A thienopyridine that is 6,7-dihydrothieno[3,2-c]pyridin-5(4H)-ylacetic acid substituted by a 2-chlorophenyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the drug  clopidogrel.
A monocarboxylic acid that is (sulfoamino)acetic acid substituted by a heptadecafluorooctyl group at the sulfur atom.
A sulfonamide that is the N-methyl derivative of perfluorooctane sulfonamidoacetic acid.

A member of the class of  morpholines that is morpholin-3-one substituted by a 2-ethyl-6-methylphenyl group at position 4 and a methyl group at position 5. It is a metabolite of metolachlor.
A member of the class of pradimicins that is isolated from the cultured broth of Actinomadura hibisca No. P157-2 (ATCC 53557).

A methanesulfonate ester that is methanesulfonic acid in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy group has been replaced by a 3,3-dimethyl-2-oxo-2,3-dihydro-1-benzofuran-5-yl group. It is a metabolite of the herbicide ethofumesate.
A monoamino-1,3,5-triazine that is 1,3,5-triazin-2-amine substituted by a methoxy group at position 4 and a methyl group at position 6. It is a metabolite of the herbicide thifensulfuron-methyl.
A benzoate ester that is methyl benzoate substituted by a sulfamoyl group at position 2. It is a metabolite of the herbicide metsulfuron-methyl.
A member of the class of  pyrazoles that is antipyrine substituted by an acetylamino group at position 4. It is a drug metabolite of metamizole.
A member of the class of phenylureas that is urea substituted by a p-cumenyl group at position 1. It is a metabolite of the herbicide isoproturon.
